%20fabrics%20made%20from%20petrochemicals%2C%20such%20as%20nylon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReformation%20aims%20to%20use%20as%20little%20new%20material%20as%20possible%20and%20reduce%20waste%20in%20order%20to%20become%20%26quot%3Bclimate%20positive%26quot%3B%20by%202025%2C%20which%20involves%20removing%20more%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20than%20the%20company%20produces.%20About%20a%20third%20of%20its%20carbon%20footprint%20comes%20from%20the%20virgin%20materials%20it%20uses%2C%20including%20cashmere%2C%20silk%2C%20and%20viscose.%20Reformation's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.thereformation.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fv1637167253%2Fpdfs%2FHow-to-be-a-Climate-Positive-business-.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroad%20map%3C%2Fa%3E%20calls%20for%20using%20more%20recycled%20wool%20and%20eliminating%20silk%2C%20as%20well%20as%20buying%20carbon%20offsets%20that%20remove%20carbon%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20as%20opposed%20to%20avoiding%20emissions.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fashion%20industry%20is%20throwing%20away%20almost%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20materials%20we%20are%20generating%20every%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Talbot%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20just%20connect%20those%20dots%20and%20circulate%20these%20raw%20materials%2C%20we%20can%20eliminate%20waste%20and%20emissions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202022%2C%20Reformation%20launched%20RefRecycling%20so%20customers%20can%20drop%20off%20their%20old%20clothes%20at%20retail%20locations.%20And%20shoppers%20won't%20find%20racks%20and%20racks%20of%20clothing%20at%20its%20stores.%20Reformation%20releases%20limited%20collections%20every%20week%2C%20and%20only%20makes%20more%20if%20the%20sales%20demand%20it%2C%20to%20limit%20waste.%20About%2016%25%20of%20its%20sales%20come%20from%20vintage%2C%20rental%2C%20or%20resale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20different%20model%20than%20fast%20fashion%2C%20which%20emits%20about%2010%25%20of%20greenhouse%20gasses%20globally%20and%20makes%2040%20billion%20garments%20every%20year%20that%20are%20never%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReformation%20is%20also%20getting%20into%20politics.%20It's%20one%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20brands%20that%20has%20endorsed%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nysenate.gov%2Flegislation%2Fbills%2F2021%2FS7428%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%20state%20and%20Congress%20that%20would%20require%20more%20transparency%20in%20fashion%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655adf6b22cf74a57399edce%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655adf6922cf74a57399edcb%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655adf6b22cf74a57399edcf%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655adf699c7d23cb3b9d2ee3%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655adf6922cf74a57399edcb%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kathleen%20Talbot%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEtosha%20Cave%2C%20Cofounder%20and%20CSO%2C%20Twelve%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Dr.%20Etosha%20Cave%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20black%20blouse%20and%20holding%20a%20silver%20reactor.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e6bbe36d588dc55ce982b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETwelve%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEtosha%20Cave%20started%20Twelve%20in%202015%20while%20she%20was%20a%20grad%20student%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20along%20with%20her%20fellow%20graduate%20students%20Kendra%20Kuhl%20and%20Nicholas%20Flanders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECave%2C%20who%20holds%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20mechanical%20engineering%2C%20and%20Kuhl%20developed%20a%20carbon-transformation%20technology%20that%20can%20take%20carbon%20dioxide%20from%20the%20air%20and%20turn%20it%20into%20products%20including%20shoes%2C%20clothes%2C%20and%20electronics.%20The%20technology%20can%20even%20make%20a%20sustainable%20aviation%20fuel%2C%20called%20E-Jet%2C%20according%20to%20Cave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCarbon%20is%20such%20a%20ubiquitous%20molecule%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20used%20in%20so%20many%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Cave%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20provide%20this%20air-based%20carbon%2C%20instead%20of%20fossil-based%20carbon%2C%20we%20can%20start%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwelve%20is%20collaborating%20with%20major%20partners%20such%20as%20Microsoft%2C%20Alaska%20Airlines%2C%20and%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20to%20advance%20the%20development%20of%20its%20sustainable%20E-Jet%20fuel.%20%26quot%3BFor%20every%20gallon%20of%20sustainable%20aviation%20fuel%20we%20can%20make%2C%20we're%20displacing%20a%20gallon%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%26quot%3B%20Cave%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20from%20grad%20school%20to%20running%20a%20startup%20has%20had%20its%20challenges%2C%20but%20for%20Cave%2C%20this%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20era%26quot%3B%20for%20climate%20tech.%20She%20cited%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20as%20an%20example%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bunique%20alignment%20of%20policy%20and%20technology%20and%20public%20opinion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20kind%20of%20an%20all-hands-on-deck%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20lots%20of%20people%20and%20lots%20of%20technologies%20working%20toward%20reducing%20our%20CO2%20emissions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655ca6b44ca513d8242cb47e%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655ca6b49c7d23cb3b9ddffa%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655ca6b44ca513d8242cb47f%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655ca6b49c7d23cb3b9ddffb%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655ca6b49c7d23cb3b9ddffa%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Etosha%20Cave%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPablo%20Ribeiro%20Dias%2C%20Cofounder%20and%20CTO%2C%20SolarCycle%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221484%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Dr.%20Pablo%20Riberio%20Dias%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20white%20button-down%20shirt%20in%20front%20of%20greenery.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e57d736d588dc55ce7789%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222226%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMarcio%20Pimenta%20for%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%202%20billion%20solar%20panels%20are%20installed%20around%20the%20world.%20That%20number%20is%20rapidly%20rising%20as%20countries%20expand%20renewable%20energy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20those%20panels%20don't%20last%20forever%2C%20and%20Pablo%20Ribeiro%20Dias%20wants%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20don't%20end%20up%20in%20a%20landfill.%20So%20he%20cofounded%20SolarCycle%2C%20a%20Texas-based%20startup%20that%20reclaims%20old%20solar%20panels%20so%20they%20can%20be%20turned%20into%20new%20ones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.solarcycle.us%2Fpress-releases%2Fsolarcycle-raises-30m-equity-financing-to-scale-advanced-recycling-for-the-solar-industry%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20raised%20%2437%20million%20so%20far%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20expects%20to%20process%20about%201%20million%20panels%20a%20year%20at%20a%20new%20recycling%20and%20manufacturing%20plant.%20SolarCycle's%20customers%20include%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20renewable-energy%20companies%20including%20%C3%98rsted%20and%20Sunrun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20can%20use%20the%20same%20resources%20for%20longer%2C%20that%20means%20less%20resources%20are%20extracted%20from%20the%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20Dias%2C%20who%20has%20two%20Ph.D.s%20and%20pioneered%20research%20on%20new%20ways%20to%20recycle%20solar%20panels%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20one%20way%20for%20us%20to%20live%20sustainably.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDias%20said%20he%20learned%20the%20value%20of%20materials%20from%20a%20young%20age%20growing%20up%20in%20Brazil%2C%20where%20throwaway%20culture%20isn't%20as%20prevalent%20as%20in%20the%20US.%20Dias%20researched%20e-waste%20recycling%20technology%20for%20cellphones%20and%20other%20electronics%2C%20which%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20his%20work%20on%20solar%20panels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESolarCycle%20says%20its%20technology%20can%20reclaim%20more%20than%2095%25%20of%20all%20the%20valuable%20materials%20in%20solar%20panels%2C%20including%20aluminum%2C%20glass%2C%20copper%2C%20silver%2C%20and%20silicon.%20These%20materials%20are%20sold%20back%20into%20the%20solar%20value%20chain.%20The%20hope%20is%20that%20by%20scaling%20a%20circular%20system%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20mining%20new%20metals%20in%20countries%20like%20Mexico%2C%20China%2C%20and%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%20will%20drop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlastics%20are%20a%20trickier%20material%2C%20Dias%20said%2C%20because%20the%20plastic%20used%20in%20solar%20panels%20is%20similar%20to%20rubber%20tires.%20Right%20now%2C%20it's%20not%20feasible%20to%20recycle%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20stage%20for%20SolarCycle%20is%20opening%20a%20second%20recycling%20plant%20in%20Phoenix%20and%20establishing%20a%20research%20and%20development%20center.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20a%20great%20position%20to%20build%20a%20real%20circular%20economy%2C%20not%20just%20a%20fairy-tale%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Dias%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C