Helion_Fact_Sheet.pdf%3Fp%3Doriginal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E500-megawatt%20power%20plant%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20steel%20plant%20owned%20by%20Nucor%2C%20America's%20biggest%20steel%20supplier%20and%20recycler.%20The%20companies%20said%20the%20operation%20could%20start%20as%20early%20as%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20fusion%20facilities%20would%20mark%20the%20dawn%20of%20a%20new%20era%20of%20energy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirtley%2C%20a%20nuclear%20and%20aerospace%20engineer%2C%20wasn't%20always%20convinced%20that%20humans%20could%20harness%20fusion%20for%20electricity%20during%20his%20lifetime.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20he%20left%20the%20field%20and%20worked%20on%20advanced%20rockets%20instead.%20But%20as%20fusion%20systems%20became%20smaller%20and%20more%20energy%20efficient%20through%20modern%20electronics%20and%20fiber%20optics%2C%20Kirtley%20saw%20a%20path%20forward.%20He%20helped%20build%20those%20fusion%20systems%20at%20MSNW%2C%20a%20research%20company%20backed%20by%20NASA%20and%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Energy.%20That%20work%20was%20spun%20off%20into%20Helion%20in%202013.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20six%20of%20Helion's%20fusion%20prototypes%20have%20set%20records%20for%20their%20energy%20output%20and%20the%20temperature%20at%20which%20they%20operate%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20210622005366%2Fen%2FHelion-Energy-Achieves-100-Million-Degrees-Celsius-Fusion-Fuel-Temperature-and-Confirms-16-Month-Continuous-Operation-of-Its-Fusion-Generator-Prototype%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20exceeding%20100%20million%20degrees%20Celsius%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20an%20ideal%20threshold%20for%20a%20power%20plant.%20The%20seventh%20prototype%2C%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20this%20year%2C%20is%20set%20to%20be%20the%20first%20to%20convert%20fusion%20energy%20into%20electricity%2C%20Kirtley%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20his%20w