20Onuigbo%20grew%20up%2C%20he%20and%20his%20neighbors%20would%20draw%20drinking%20water%20from%20six%20springs%2C%20and%20there%20were%20gullies%20where%20he%20and%20his%20friends%20from%20primary%20school%20would%20go%20to%20pick%20snails%20and%20chase%20rabbits.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Onuigbo%20returned%20to%20his%20village%20after%20finishing%20his%20college%20studies%20and%20a%20year%20of%20national%20service%2C%20he%20discovered%20that%20five%20of%20the%20springs%20had%20run%20dry%20and%20erosion%20had%20made%20many%20of%20the%20gullies%20in%20which%20he%20had%20once%20played%20too%20dangerous%20for%20people%20to%20enter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20experiences%20made%20Onuigbo%20realize%20how%20much%20the%20climate%20crisis%20was%20hurting%20his%20country.%20As%20a%20member%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20of%20Nigeria%2C%20Onuigbo%20sponsored%20a%20climate%20bill%20that%20was%20signed%20into%20law%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20requires%20the%20government%20to%20draw%20up%20plans%20on%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20establish%20a%20carbon%20budget.%20The%20law%20also%20set%20up%20funding%20for%20dealing%20with%20emerging%20climate%20hazards%20and%20required%20many%20businesses%20to%20meet%20annual%20emissions-reduction%20targets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnuigbo%20said%20before%20the%20law%20was%20passed%2C%20government%20directors%20in%20various%20agencies%20often%20tried%20to%20tackle%20the%20problem%20piecemeal.%20%26quot%3BThey%20preferred%20working%20in%20silos%2C%20not%20reporting%20to%20anybody%2C%20not%20being%20coordinated.%20And%20that%2C%20for%20me%2C%20is%20absolutely%20unproductive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Now%2C%20Onuigbo%20said%2C%20the%20president%20appoints%20people%20to%20oversee%20these%20efforts.%20That%20means%20there's%20greater%20accountability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20legal%20framework%2C%20Onuigbo%2C%20who%20left%20the%20Nigerian%20House%20of%20Representatives%20in%20June%20after%20eight%20years%2C%20said%20the%20bill%20helped%20bring%20everyday%20Nigerians'%20attention%20to%20the%20effects%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20on%20the%20country.%20%26quot%3BYou%20are%20getting%20conversations%20on%20climate%20change%20from%20different%20angles%20within%20the%20nation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnuigbo%20is%20currently%20a%20board%20member%20and%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20committee%20on%20security%2C%20special%20interventions%2C%20and%20climate%20change%20of%20the%20North%20East%20Development%20Commission.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655b2ba09c7d23cb3b9d34f6%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655b2ba022cf74a57399f2d2%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655b2ba09c7d23cb3b9d34f7%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655b2ba022cf74a57399f2d3%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655b2ba022cf74a57399f2d2%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rep.%20Samuel%20Onuigbo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMatt%20Petersen%2C%20President%20and%20CEO%2C%20Los%20Angeles%20Cleantech%20Incubator%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223540%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Matt%20Petersen%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20gray%20suit%20jacket%20and%20light%20blue%20button-down%20shirt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e681e3cc84b4dfa003393%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225310%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELACI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMatt%20Petersen%20has%20been%20an%20environmental%20leader%20for%20three%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Modesto%2C%20California%2C%20native%20spent%20the%20first%20part%20of%20his%20career%20advocating%20for%20nuclear%20demilitarization%20and%20pioneering%20the%20green-building%20movement%20before%20becoming%20Los%20Angeles'%20first%20chief%20sustainability%20officer%20in%202013.%20He%20also%20created%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fclimatemayors.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EClimate%20Mayors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20250%20US%20mayors%20fighting%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20six%20years%2C%20Petersen%20has%20led%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20Cleantech%20Incubator%2C%20or%20LACI%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20helps%20startups%20scale%20their%20low-carbon%20transportation%20and%20energy%20technologies%20in%20communities%20exposed%20to%20high%20levels%20of%20pollution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetersen%20has%20expanded%20LACI's%20work%20beyond%20just%20a%20startup%20incubator.%20The%20nonprofit%20launched%20the%20Transportation%20Electrification%20Partnership%20in%20May%202018%2C%20which%20pools%20public%20and%20private%20money%20and%20invests%20it%20in%20pilot%20programs%20aimed%20at%20cleaning%20up%20LA's%20busy%20ports%2C%20freeways%2C%20and%20local%20communities.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20drive%20down%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20and%20air%20pollution%20from%20heavy-duty%20shipping%20trucks%20and%20personal%20cars%20by%202028%2C%20when%20LA%20is%20hosting%20the%20Olympic%20and%20Paralympic%20Games.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELACI%20startups%20are%20testing%20electric-vehicle%20car-sharing%20at%20public-housing%20developments%20in%20East%20LA%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flaincubator.org%2Fzedz%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezero-emissions%20delivery%20zone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Santa%20Monica.%20The%20nonprofit%20has%20also%20assembled%20funding%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspectrumnews1.com%2Fca%2Fla-west%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F25%2Fport-of-la-s-first-ev-truck-charging-depot-gets-funding%3Fcid%3Did-app15_m-share_s-web_cmp-app_launch_august2020_c-producer_posts_po-organic%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectric-truck%20charging%20stations%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Port%20of%20LA%20and%20Long%20Beach%2C%20where%20some%2040%25%20of%20the%20country's%20shipping%20containers%20arrive%20before%20dirty%20diesel-engine%20trucks%20drive%20the%20goods%20around%20the%20region.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELACI%20is%20expanding%20its%20work%20into%20clean%20energy%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flaincubator.org%2Fclean-energy-2028-roadmap%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleasing%20a%20road%20map%20in%20October%3C%2Fa%3E%20focused%20on%20electrifying%20buildings%20and%20deploying%20smaller%20renewable-energy%20systems%20powered%20by%20solar%2C%20battery%20storage%2C%20and%20other%20technologies.%20LACI%20also%20has%20a%20workforce%20development%20program%20that%20trains%20about%20300%20people%20each%20year%2C%20including%20an%20all-female%20course%20on%20EV%20charging%20maintenance%2C%20Petersen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetersen%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20wants%20the%20green%20economy%20to%20be%20inclusive%20of%20all%20races%2C%20classes%2C%20and%20genders.%20Petersen%20worked%20with%20Habitat%20for%20Humanity%2C%20helping%20to%20rebuild%20New%20Orleans%20after%20Hurricane%20Katrina%2C%20and%20he%20saw%20the%20barriers%20families%20faced%20to%20live%20in%20affordable%2C%20energy-efficient%20homes%20that%20didn't%20leave%20them%20with%20high%20utility%20bills%20and%20poor%20indoor-air%20quality.%20Petersen%20said%20he's%20also%20had%20many%20female%20mentors%20who%20instilled%20the%20importance%20of%20empowering%20women%20in%20the%20workforce.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChanging%20the%20composition%20of%20our%20startups%20to%20be%20more%20diverse%20was%20important%20to%20me%20so%20LACI%20better%20represents%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20population%20of%20Los%20Angeles%2C%26quot%3B%20Petersen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655d52454ca513d8242d63a2%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d524422cf74a5739b4c04%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d52449c7d23cb3b9e8bd0%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d52459c7d23cb3b9e8bd3%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d524422cf74a5739b4c04%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matt%20Petersen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMaisa%20Rojas%2C%20Chile's%20environment%20minister%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222252%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Maisa%20Rojas%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20navy%20sleeveless%20shirt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e6925b788914e555413da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223377%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGobierno%20de%20Chile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20world%20leaders%20gathered%20in%20Egypt%20for%20the%20UN's%20annual%20climate%20summit.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20important%20outcomes%20of%20that%20event%20was%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bloss%20and%20damage%26quot%3B%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20effectively%20a%20pot%20of%20money%20that%20poor%2C%20climate-vulnerable%20countries%20can%20tap%20into%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20damage%20caused%20by%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20Wealthy%20powers%20such%20as%20the%20US%20and%20European%20Union%2C%20which%20are%20historically%20responsible%20for%20the%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20warming%20the%20planet%2C%20are%20expected%20to%20contribute.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaisa%20Rojas%2C%20Chile's%20environment%20minister%2C%20led%20those%20negotiations%20with%20Jennifer%20Morgan%2C%20Germany's%20special%20envoy%20for%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERojas%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it%20was%20an%20incredible%20privilege%20to%20have%20been%20asked%20by%20Egyptian%20officials%20to%20handle%20the%20talks.%20But%20at%20the%20outset%2C%20there%20was%20no%20guarantee%20of%20success.%20It%20wasn't%20clear%20whether%20loss%20and%20damage%20would%20be%20on%20the%20agenda%20at%20all%2C%20given%20the%20decades%20of%20opposition%20from%20rich%20countries.%20After%20that%20hurdle%2C%20days%20of%20negotiations%20ensued%20over%20what%20a%20deal%20would%20look%20like.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20momentum%20was%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Rojas%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20a%20coalition%20of%20small%20island%20states%20and%20developing%20countries%20known%20as%20the%20Group%20of%2077%20and%20China%20was%20united%20in%20the%20cause.%20%26quot%3BVery%20late%20in%20the%20negotiations%2C%20the%20EU%20decided%20to%20say%20yes%20to%20a%20fund%2C%20and%20then%20we'd%20sort%20out%20the%20details%20afterward.%20That%20was%20a%20very%20exciting%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carbonbrief.org%2Fqa-the-fight-over-the-loss-and-damage-fund-for-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethose%20details%20are%20starting%20to%20take%20shape%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20proposal%20that%20could%20be%20adopted%20during%20the%20UN%20climate%20summit%20in%20Dubai%2C%20which%20starts%20in%20November.%20Many%20issues%20remain%20contentious%2C%20such%20as%20which%20countries%20are%20eligible%20for%20the%20funds%2C%20which%20have%20to%20contribute%20money%2C%20and%20how%20much.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20UN-commissioned%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lse.ac.uk%2Fgranthaminstitute%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2FIHLEG-Finance-for-Climate-Action-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20based%20on%20recent%20climate-fueled%20disasters%2C%20the%20future%20costs%20of%20loss%20and%20damage%20could%20be%20as%20much%20as%20%24150%20billion%20to%20%24300%20billion%20by%202030%20based.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20way%2C%20we%20are%20admitting%20that%20we%20as%20humanity%20have%20failed%20to%20address%20climate%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Rojas%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%20there%20are%20irreversible%20losses%20that%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%20This%20fund%20can%20help%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20and%20the%20most%20affected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERojas%2C%20who%20holds%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20atmospheric%20physics%2C%20also%20wants%20to%20ensure%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20populations%20in%20Chile%20benefit%20from%20the%20green%20transformation%20the%20country%20is%20undergoing%2C%20she%20said.%20Rojas%20took%20office%20in%20March%202022%20under%20President%20Gabriel%20Boric%20and%20is%20responsible%20for%20implementing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gob.cl%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fa-milestone-in-chiles-environmental-history-from-today-we-have-our-first-framework-law-on-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20climate%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20requires%20Chile%20to%20become%20carbon-neutral%20by%202050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20holding%20political%20office%2C%20Rojas%20was%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Climate%20and%20Resilience%20Research%20at%20the%20Universidad%20de%20Chile%20and%20a%20lead%20author%20on%20the%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655d47919c7d23cb3b9e8abf%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d47919c7d23cb3b9e8ac0%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d47919c7d23cb3b9e8ac1%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d47919c7d23cb3b9e8ac2%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d47919c7d23cb3b9e8ac0%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maisa%20Rojas%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPatricio%20Sep%C3%BAlveda%2C%20Head%20of%20public%20debt%20management%20office%2C%20Chile%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222987%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Patricio%20Sepulveda%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20navy%20suit%20and%20tie.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e698ab788914e55541459%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPaula%20Far%C3%ADas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChile%20is%20known%20as%20a%20trailblazer%20in%20the%20sustainable-bond%20market.%20As%20of%20this%20year%2C%20the%20country%20has%20%2443.5%20billion%20in%20public%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20its%20total%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20tied%20to%20achieving%20its%20climate%20and%20social%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20architect%20of%20the%20program%20is%20Patricio%20Sep%C3%BAlveda.%20His%20office%20developed%20financial%20frameworks%20that%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20Chile%20in%202019%20to%20become%20the%20first%20country%20in%20the%20Americas%20to%20issue%20a%20green%20bond%2C%20creating%20a%20model%20for%20other%20countries%20in%20the%20region.%20The%20bond%20funds%20projects%20to%20electrify%20public%20transportation%2C%20expand%20renewable%20energy%2C%20and%20make%20buildings%20more%20energy%20efficient.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20have%20more%20sustainable%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Sep%C3%BAlveda%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20grow%20our%20economy%20without%20forgetting%20about%20protecting%20the%20environment.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Sep%C3%BAlveda%20has%20expanded%20Chile's%20bond%20program%20for%20sustainable%20development.%20In%202022%2C%20Chile%20became%20the%20first%20country%20in%20the%20world%20to%20issue%20a%20sustainability-linked%20bond%2C%20or%20SLB.%20Unlike%20green%20or%20social%20bonds%20that%20are%20tied%20to%20specific%20projects%2C%20SLBs%20are%20attached%20to%20achieving%20longer-term%20targets.%20If%20those%20targets%20aren't%20met%2C%20Chile%20will%20face%20financial%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChile%20aims%20to%20peak%20its%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20by%202025%20and%20achieve%20net-zero%20emissions%20by%20midcentury.%20That%20goal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gob.cl%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fa-milestone-in-chiles-environmental-history-from-today-we-have-our-first-framework-law-on-climate-change%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20enshrined%20in%20the%20country's%20climate%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20last%20year.%20Chile%20also%20wants%2060%25%20of%20its%20electricity%20to%20come%20from%20renewable%20energy%20by%202032%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20to%2027%25%20in%202021.%20On%20the%20issue%20of%20gender%20equality%2C%20the%20country%20is%20pushing%20for%20women%20to%20represent%2040%25%20of%20corporate%20board%20directors%20by%202031.%20Women%20currently%20only%20make%20up%20about%2013%25%20of%20board%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESep%C3%BAlveda%20said%20SLBs%20are%20a%20powerful%20way%20to%20ensure%20Chile%20continues%20making%20progress%20toward%20its%20sustainability%20goals%2C%20regardless%20of%20who's%20in%20charge%20politically.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20next%20goal%20is%20to%20incorporate%20biodiversity%20goals%20into%20Chile's%20SLBs%2C%20because%20protecting%20forests%20and%20oceans%20is%20key%20to%20solving%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655d262522cf74a5739b3b22%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d262522cf74a5739b3b21%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d262522cf74a5739b3b23%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d262522cf74a5739b3b24%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d262522cf74a5739b3b21%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Patricio%20Sep%C3%BAlveda%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJiqiu%20%26quot%3BJQ%26quot%3B%20Yuan%2C%20Vice%20president%20of%20engineering%2C%20National%20Institute%20of%20Building%20Sciences%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20Jiqiu%20(JQ)%20Yuan%2C%20who%20is%20wearing%20a%20light%20blue%20button-down%20shirt%20and%20a%20navy%20blazer.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6552567858cf5fbccb95940f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENational%20Institute%20of%20Building%20Sciences%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJQ%20Yuan%20works%20toward%20making%20buildings%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20communities%20resilient%20against%20natural%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20frequent%20extreme%20weather%20events%20predicted%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20Yuan%20said%20that%20it's%20vital%20that%20we're%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20for%20life.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it's%20not%20easy%20to%20sell%20that%20concept%20because%20when%20you%20have%20a%20building%20better%20and%20stronger%2C%20it%20always%20comes%20with%20a%20cost%2C%26quot%3B%20Yuan%20said.%20But%2C%20he%20said%2C%20investing%20in%20resilience%20now%20could%20have%20a%20huge%20payoff%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYuan%2C%20who%20has%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20structural%20engineering%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Kansas%2C%20led%20a%20study%20that%20found%20for%20every%20dollar%20spent%20by%20federal%20agencies%20on%20natural-hazard%20mitigation%2C%20%246%20was%20saved.%20The%20study%20also%20found%20that%20adopting%20the%20latest%20building-code%20requirements%20saved%20%2411%20for%20every%20%241%20invested.%20%26quot%3BThe%20return%20on%20investment%20is%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20Yuan%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Yuan%2C%20incentivizing%20the%20private%20sector%20to%20invest%20in%20provisions%20to%20mitigate%20against%20natural%20disasters%20is%20hugely%20important.%20He%20recently%20coauthored%20a%20road%20map%20outlining%20how%20to%20create%20%26quot%3Bmutual%20benefit%26quot%3B%20for%20both%20the%20private%20sector%20and%20society%20when%20responding%20to%20extreme%20weather.%20Yuan%20is%20also%20working%20on%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Building%20Sciences'%20Lifeline%20Infrastructure%20Hub%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20create%20public-private%20partnerships%20at%20the%20community%20level%20to%20aid%20in%20disaster%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20building%20codes%2C%20Yuan%20said%2C%20are%20based%20on%20what%20has%20happened%20in%20the%20past%20and%20take%20the%20climate%20crisis%20into%20account.%20He%20said%20we%20needed%20to%20bring%20together%20the%20current%20science%20with%20engineering%20and%20%26quot%3Bdesign%20for%20the%20future%20climate-change%20conditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22es%5C%22%20data-image-ids%3D%5C%22%5B%26quot%3B655d442c9c7d23cb3b9e8a2e%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d442c4ca513d8242d619a%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d442c4ca513d8242d619b%26quot%3B%2C%20%26quot%3B655d442c9c7d23cb3b9e8a2f%26quot%3B%5D%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cpicture%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20data-src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d442c4ca513d8242d619a%3Fwidth%3D350%26amp%3Bauto%3Dwebp%26amp%3Bquality%3D100%2C100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jiqiu%20%E2%80%9CJQ%E2%80%9D%20Yuan%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fpicture%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ch2%3ECredits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cspan%3ESeries%20Editor%3A%20%3