ce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-housing-market-economy-japan-jpmorgan-financial-investors-geopolitics-demographics-2023-8%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BJapanification%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20all%20point%20to%20disinflation%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20shifting%20demographics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20more%20and%20more%20countries%20age%2C%20there%20will%20likely%20be%20significant%20implications%20for%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Jen%20and%20Freire%20said.%20%26quot%3BCountries%20will%20invariably%20fight%20this%20demographic%20headwind%2C%20but%20the%20end%20result%20of%20ageing%20will%20likely%20not%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20population%20of%20Japan%20%E2%80%94%20the%20oldest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20began%20to%20meaningfully%20age%20in%201990%2C%20and%20since%20then%20its%20inflation%20and%20interest%20rates%20have%20dropped.%20Three%20decades%20of%20low%20inflation%20there%20came%20despite%20the%20Bank%20of%20Japan's%20bid%20to%20stimulate%20demand%20with%20unconventional%20monetary%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThough%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-japanification-financial-markets-japan-jpmorgan-deflation-property-2023-8%5C%22%3Ebursting%20of%20the%20triple%20bubbles%3C%2Fa%3E%20(equity%2C%20property%2C%20and%20investment%20bubbles)%20in%20Japan%20in%201990%20may%20have%20had%20depressive%20effects%20on%20economic%20growth%20and%20inflation%20in%20the%20ensuing%20years%2C%20through%20balance%20sheet%20recessionary%20dynamics%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20blame%20what%20happened%20in%201990%20for%20what%20is%20happening%20now%20%E2%80%93%20a%20third%20of%20a%20century%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20Eurizon's%20calculations%2C%20Japan's%20labor%20force%20peaked%20in%202019%2C%20at%201.7%20times%20its%20size%20from%201950%2C%20which%20suggests%20an%20average%20annual%20labor%20force%20growth%20rate%20of%200.77%20percent%20a%20year%20through%20the%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20initially%20peaked%20in%201997%2C%20but%20dramatic%20policy%20efforts%20helped%20delay%20the%20ultimate%20peak%20by%20nearly%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20China's%20labor%20force%20peak%20from%202018%20will%20likely%20be%20pushed%20back%20by%20new%20policies.%20The%20US%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20projected%20to%20see%20its%20labor%20force%20peak%20delayed%20due%20to%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221405%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eurizon's%20labor%20force%20peak%20calculations%2C%20November%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6564a17ffe5bc6545ebc467c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221276%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEurizon's%20calculations%20of%20labor%20force%20peaks%20for%20China%2C%20Japan%2C%20the%20EU%2C%20India%2C%20and%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EEurizon%20SLJ%20Capital%20Limited%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20countries%20follow%20Japan's%20demographic%20path%2C%20inflation%20should%20follow%20a%20similar%20trajectory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20could%20not%20have%20altered%20the%20relationship%20between%20demographics%20and%20inflation%2C%20in%20Eurizon's%20view.%20Rather%2C%20the%20sharp%20drop%20and%20then%20gradual%20recovery%20of%20employment%20has%20allowed%20for%20inflation%20to%20fall%20without%20a%20spike%20in%20the%20unemployment%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20short%20run%2C%20we%20can%20even%20see%20some%20risk%20of%20outright%20deflation%20because%20the%20general%20price%20levels%20seem%20already%20too%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Eurizon%20economists%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20we%20see%20the%20new%20steady-state%20inflation%20being%20only%20marginally%20higher%20than%20the%20lows%20witnessed%20before%20the%20Pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBank%20of%20America%