20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftv-and-radio%2F2023%2Fnov%2F19%2Fim-a-celebrity-get-me-out-of-here-review-cakewalk-for-nigel-farage%5C%22%3EI%E2%80%99m%20a%20Celebrity%20Get%20me%20out%20of%20Here!%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fpauline-hanson-built-a-political-career-on-white-victimhood-and-brought-far-right-rhetoric-to-the-mainstream-134661%5C%22%3EPauline%20Hanson%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20extreme%20right%20party%20in%20Australia%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20did%20when%20she%20was%20invited%20on%20Dancing%20with%20the%20Stars%20just%20a%20moment%20after%20her%20political%20career%20plummeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contradiction%20in%20addressing%20the%20rise%20of%20far-right%20politics%20in%20public%20discourse%20could%20not%20be%20starker.%20And%20yet%2C%20it%20goes%20far%20deeper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20should%20be%20obvious%20to%20anyone%20concerned%20about%20these%20politics%20and%20the%20threat%20they%20pose%20to%20democracy%20and%20certain%20communities%2C%20that%20humanising%20their%20leaders%20through%20fun%20reality%20TV%20shows%20or%20coverage%20of%20their%20hobbies%20rather%20than%20politics%20only%20serves%20to%20normalise%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20less%20obvious%20and%20yet%20just%20as%20damaging%20is%20the%20hyped%20coverage%20of%20the%20threat.%20Milei%20and%20Wilders%20are%20not%20%E2%80%9Cshocks%E2%80%9D.%20The%20resurgence%20of%20reactionary%20politics%20is%20entirely%20predictable%20and%20has%20been%20traced%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Yet%20every%20victory%20or%20rise%20is%20analysed%20as%20new%20and%20unexpected%20rather%20than%20part%20of%20a%20longer%2C%20wider%20process%20in%20which%20we%20are%20all%20implicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20goes%20for%20%E2%80%9Cpopulism%E2%80%9D.%20All%20serious%20research%20on%20the%20matter%20points%20to%20the%20populist%20nature%20of%20these%20parties%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F13569317.2020.1844372%5C%22%3Esecondary%20at%20best%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20compared%20to%20their%20far-right%20qualities.%20Yet%2C%20whether%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F0263395720955036%5C%22%3Emedia%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Fpolitical-science-research-and-methods%2Farticle%2Fwhats-in-a-buzzword-a-systematic-review-of-the-state-of-populism-research-in-political-science%2FD9CD5E7E13DFA30FD05D41F32E6C122B%5C%22%3Eacademia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20populism%20is%20generally%20used%20carelessly%20as%20a%20key%20defining%20feature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20%E2%80%9Cpopulist%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20more%20accurate%20but%20also%20stigmatising%20terms%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfar-right%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cracist%E2%80%9D%20acts%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.populismus.gr%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2FWP4-glynos-mondon-final-upload.pdf%5C%22%3Ea%20key%20legitimiser%20of%20far-right%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20lends%20these%20parties%20and%20politicians%20a%20veneer%20of%20democratic%20support%20through%20the%20etymological%20link%20to%20the%20people%20and%20erases%20their%20deeply%20elitist%20nature%20%E2%80%93%20what%20my%20co-author%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lancaster.ac.uk%2Fsociology%2Fpeople%2Faaron-winter%5C%22%3EAaron%20Winter%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20I%20have%20termed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fen-gb%2Fproducts%2F837-reactionary-democracy%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Creactionary%20democracy%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20this%20points%20to%20is%20that%20the%20processes%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F13569317.2021.1949829%5C%22%3Emainstreaming%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F09579265221095406%5C%22%3Enormalisation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20far-right%20politics%20have%20much%20to%20do%20with%20the%20mainstream%20itself%2C%20if%20not%20more%20than%20with%20the%20far%20right.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20can%20be%20no%20mainstreaming%20without%20the%20mainstream%20accepting%20such%20ideas%20in%20its%20fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20mainstreaming%20process%20has%20involved%20platforming%2C%20hyping%20and%20legitimising%20far-right%20ideas%20while%20seemingly%20opposing%20them%20and%20denying%20responsibility%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20would%20be%20naive%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20mainstream%20media%20tell%20us%20what%20to%20think%2C%20it%20is%20equally%20naive%20to%20ignore%20that%20it%20plays%20a%20key%20role%20regarding%20what%20we%20think%20about.%20As%20I%20argued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F02633957221104726%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20recent%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%9Cimmigration%20as%20a%20major%20concern%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%20concern%20only%20exists%20when%20respondents%20think%20of%20their%20country%20as%20a%20whole.%20It%20disappears%20when%20they%20think%20about%20their%20own%20day-to-day%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20points%20to%20the%20mediated%20nature%20of%20our%20understanding%20of%20wider%20society%20which%20is%20essential%20if%20we%20are%20to%20think%20of%20the%20world%20beyond%20our%20immediate%20surrounding.%20Yet%20while%20essential%2C%20it%20relies%20on%20the%20need%20for%20trusted%20sources%20of%20information%20who%20decide%20what%20is%20worth%20priming%20and%20how%20to%20frame%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20very%20responsibility%20that%20much%20of%20our%20media%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fnewe.12306%5C%22%3Ecurrently%20given%20up%20on%20or%20pretend%20they%20do%20not%20hold%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20if%20their%20editorial%20choices%20were%20random%20occurrences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20not%20have%20been%20clearer%20than%20when%20the%20%3Cem%3EGuardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20launched%20a%20lengthy%20series%20on%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20new%20populism%E2%80%9D%20in%202018%2C%20headlining%20its%20opening%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2Fpolitical-science%2F2018%2Fnov%2F20%2Fwhy-is-populism-suddenly-so-sexy-the-reasons-are-many%5C%22%3Eeditorial%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20populism%20suddenly%20all%20the%20rage%3F%20In%201998%2C%20about%20300%20Guardian%20articles%20mentioned%20populism.%20In%202016%2C%202%2C000%20did.%20What%20happened%3F%E2%80%9D.%20At%20no%20point%20did%20any%20of%20the%20articles%20in%20the%20series%20reflect%20upon%20the%20simple%20fact%20that%20the%20decisions%20of%20Guardian%20editors%20may%20have%20played%20a%20role%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F0263395720955036%5C%22%3Eincreased%20use%20of%20the%20term%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20top-down%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20blame%20is%20diverted%20onto%20conveniently%20%E2%80%9Csilent%20majorities%E2%80%9D%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F00380261231186021%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cleft-behind%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20a%20fantasised%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F1070289X.2018.1552440%3FjournalCode%3Dgide20%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cwhite%20working%20class%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20too%20often%20view%20the%20far%20right%20as%20an%20outsider%20%E2%80%93%20something%20separate%20from%20ourselves%20and%20distinct%20from%20our%20norms%20and%20mainstream.%20This%20ignores%20deeply%20entrenched%20structural%20inequalities%20and%20forms%20of%20oppression%20core%20to%20our%20societies.%20This%20is%20something%20I%20noted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1057%2Fs41269-022-00271-6%5C%22%3Erecent%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20race%20and%20whiteness%20in%20academic%20discussion%20of%20such%20politics%20is%20striking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20analysis%20of%20the%20titles%20and%20abstracts%20of%20over%202%2C500%20academic%20articles%20in%20the%20field%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years%20showed%20that%20academics%20choose%20to%20frame%20their%20research%20away%20from%20such%20issues.%20Instead%2C%20we%20witness%20either%20a%20euphemisation%20or%20exceptionalisation%20of%20far-right%20politics%2C%20through%20a%20focus%20on%20topics%20such%20as%20elections%20and%20immigration%20rather%20than%20the%20wider%20structures%20at%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20therefore%2C%20leaves%20us%20with%20the%20need%20to%20reckon%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbath-ac-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com%2Fprimo-explore%2Ffulldisplay%3Fdocid%3D44BAT_ALMA_DS21135007360002761%26context%3DL%26vid%3D44BAT_VU1%26lang%3Den_US%26search_scope%3DCSCOP_44BAT_DEEP%26adaptor%3DLocal%2520Search%2520Engine%26tab%3Dlocal%26query%3Dany%2Ccontains%2Ckaty%2520brown%5C%22%3Ecrucial%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20mainstream%20plays%20in%20mainstreaming.%20Elite%20actors%20with%20privileged%20access%20to%20shaping%20public%20discourse%20through%20the%20media%2C%20politics%20and%20academia%20are%20not%20sitting%20within%20the%20ramparts%20of%20a%20mainstream%20fortress%20of%20good%20and%20justice%20besieged%20by%20growing%20waves%20of%20populism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20participating%20in%20an%20arena%20where%20power%20is%20deeply%20unevenly%20distributed%2C%20where%20the%20structural%20inequalities%20the%20far%20right%20wants%20to%20strengthen%20are%20also%20often%20core%20to%20our%20systems%20and%20where%20the%20rights%20of%20minoritised%20communities%20are%20precarious%20and%20unfulfilled.%20They%20have%20therefore%20a%20particular%20responsibility%20towards%20democracy%20and%20cannot%20blame%20the%20situation%20we%20all%20find%20ourselves%20in%20on%20others%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20it%20be%20the%20far%20right%2C%20fantasised%20silent%20majorities%20or%20minoritised%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitting%20on%20the%20fence%20is%20not%20an%20option%20for%20anyone%20who%20plays%20a%20role%20in%20shaping%20public%20discourse.%20This%20means%20self-reflection%20and%20self-criticism%20must%20be%20central%20to%20our%20ethos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20cannot%20pretend%20to%20stand%20against%20the%20far%20right%20while%20referring%20to%20its%20politics%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2018%2Fnov%2F22%2Fhillary-clinton-europe-must-curb-immigration-stop-populists-trump-brexit%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Clegitimate%20concerns%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20must%20stand%20unequivocally%20by%20and%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmanchesteruniversitypress.co.uk%2F9781526157966%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20service%20of%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20one%20of%20the%20communities%20at%20the%20sharp%20end%20of%20oppression.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F218536%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Faurelien-mondon-3467%5C%22%3EAurelien%20Mondon%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Politics%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-bath-1325%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Bath%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Flook-to-the-mainstream-to-explain-the-rise-of-the-far-right-218536%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701082850000%2C%22visual%22