n-descent-shot-in-vermont-suspect-held%2Farticleshow%2F105529780.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fthree-students-of-palestinian-descent-shot-in-vermont-suspect-held%2Famp_articleshow%2F105529780.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fthree-students-of-palestinian-descent-shot-in-vermont-suspect-held%2Famp_articleshow%2F105529780.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Weight%20of%20the%20World%20and%20Vikram%20Harijan's%20Shoulders%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131120%2FIMG-20231122-WA0134.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9CIf%20Lord%20Ram%20was%20alive%20today%2C%20I%20would%20have%20sent%20him%20to%20jail%20under%20section%20302%20of%20the%20IPC%20for%20the%20murder%20of%20Rishi%20Shambuk.%20And%20if%20Lord%20Krishna%20lived%20today%2C%20I%20would%20have%20sent%20him%20to%20jail%20under%20a%20case%20for%20sexual%20harassment%20of%20women.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20when%20Vikram%20Harijan%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20who%20teaches%20ancient%20and%20medieval%20history%20at%20the%20Allahabad%20University%2C%20posted%20this%20provocatively-worded%20tweet%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20it%20triggered%20a%20barrage%20of%20outrage%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20belongs%20to%20a%20Dalit%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20302%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20deals%20with%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2022%2C%20Prayagraj%20police%20lodged%20an%20FIR%20against%20him%20for%20the%20tweet%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20regularly%20insulting%20Hindu%20deities%20through%20%E2%80%9Cindecent%20and%20hateful%20comments.%E2%80%9D%20The%20police%20acted%20on%20a%20complaint%20by%20some%20right-wing%20groups%2C%20including%20the%20Bajrang%20Dal%2C%20and%20booked%20Harijan%20under%20Sections%20153A%20(promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups)%20and%20295A%20(deliberate%20and%20malicious%20act%20to%20outrage%20religious%20feelings)%20of%20the%20IPC%20and%20Section%2066%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEvery%20other%20day%2C%20Harijan%20insults%20Hindu%20deities%20and%20this%20has%20created%20anger%20among%20students%20and%20also%20hurt%20the%20Hindu%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Shubham%2C%20a%20Bajrang%20Dal%20activist%2C%20in%20the%20FIR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20approached%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20pleading%20that%20the%20FIR%20against%20him%20be%20quashed.%20During%20the%20hearing%20of%20the%20petition%2C%20however%2C%20he%20sought%20protection%20under%20Section%2041-A%20of%20the%20CrPC%2C%20which%20stipulates%20that%20a%20person%20must%20be%20served%20notice%20by%20the%20police%20prior%20to%20his%20or%20her%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%208%2C%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Ashwani%20Kumar%20Mishra%20and%20Syed%20Aftab%20Husain%20Rizvi%20ruled%20that%20since%20the%20FIR%20prima%20facie%20disclosed%20commissioning%20of%20cognisable%20offence%2C%20it%20could%20not%20be%20quashed.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20directed%20the%20state%20authorities%20to%20ensure%20compliance%20of%20Section%2041-A%20of%20CrPC%20if%20its%20provisions%20were%20attracted%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Harijan%20received%20legal%20relief%20against%20arbitrary%20arrest%2C%20his%20troubles%20did%20not%20end%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUniversity%20serves%20notice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20November%2021%2C%20the%20university%20served%20him%20a%20show%20cause%20notice%20to%20submit%20his%20explanation%20for%20%E2%80%9Cposting%20outrageous%20comments%20against%20Hindu%20deities%20and%20culture%E2%80%9D%20on%20social%20media%20platforms%20within%20seven%20working%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20only%20the%20latest%20controversy%20that%20the%20outspoken%20Dalit%20professor%2C%20knowing%20for%20unabashedly%20voicing%20his%20critique%20of%20the%20caste%20system%20and%20dogmas%20of%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20has%20found%20himself%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years.%20He%20has%20invited%20the%20wrath%20of%20both%20right-wing%20groups%20as%20well%20as%20the%20university%20administration%20through%20his%20blunt%20articulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202019%2C%20the%20central%20varsity%20has%20served%20him%20notice%20and%20right-wing%20groups%20have%20registered%20complaints%20against%20him%20for%20targeting%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20on%20at%20least%20two%20other%20occasions.%20For%20the%20university%20and%20his%20critics%2C%20he%20is%20a%20provocateur.%20But%20for%20Harijan%2C%20he%20is%20expressing%20his%20freedom%20to%20rationally%20critique%20social%20practices%20and%20ideas%20linked%20to%20caste%2C%20a%20subject%20he%20feels%20strongly%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Harijan%20said%20he%20used%20the%20references%20to%20the%20Hindu%20deities%20in%20his%20quest%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdevelop%20rationality%E2%80%9D%20among%20students%20and%20demonstrate%20to%20them%20the%20difference%20between%20modern%20democracy%20and%20autocratic%20states%20in%20ancient%2C%20medieval%20and%20modern%20periods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDemocracy%20means%20a%20constitutional%20life%20based%20on%20rule%20of%20law.%20In%20that%20context%2C%20I%20stated%20this%20example%20that%20had%20these%20deities%20committed%20these%20acts%20in%20these%20times%2C%20what%20would%20have%20been%20the%20response%20to%20them.%20It%20was%20an%20emotional%20step%20towards%20teaching%20rationality%20to%20students%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20363px)%2085vw%2C%20363px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131639%2FScreenshot-2023-11-27-at-1.16.26%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22363%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131639%2FScreenshot-2023-11-27-at-1.16.26%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%20660w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131639%2FScreenshot-2023-11-27-at-1.16.26%25E2%2580%25AFPM-205x300.png%20205w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686529%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVikram%20Harijan.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShambuk%20and%20the%20rage%20of%20the%20years%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20restricted%20to%20academic%20expression%2C%20the%20motivation%20to%20use%20these%20references%20also%20stems%20from%20his%20%E2%80%9Cinternal%20rage%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20caste%20discrimination%20and%20his%20lived%20experiences%20as%20a%20Dalit.%20The%20story%20of%20Shambuk%2C%20a%20reference%20to%20which%20has%20landed%20him%20in%20a%20soup%2C%20has%20often%20been%20used%20by%20scholars%20to%20illustrate%20caste%20hierarchy%20and%20discrimination%20in%20the%20Ramayana.%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20refers%20to%20it%20in%20his%20seminal%20work%20%3Cem%3EAnnihilation%20of%20Caste%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20also%20details%20it%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ERiddles%20of%20Hinduism%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20was%20posthumously%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20goes%20that%20when%20Ram%20was%20ruling%20Ayodhya%20as%20a%20king%2C%20a%20Brahmin%20man%20comes%20to%20him%2C%20weeping%2C%20with%20his%20dead%20son%20in%20his%20arms.%20The%20Brahmin%20concludes%20that%20his%20son%20died%20because%20the%20king%20may%20have%20committed%20a%20sin.%20A%20sage%20informs%20Ram%20that%20the%20Brahmin%E2%80%99s%20son%20died%20because%20a%20Shudra%20man%20in%20the%20kingdom%20was%20practising%20penance%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20dharma.%20Ram%20goes%20to%20the%20said%20Shudra%20ascetic%2C%20Shambuk%2C%20who%20informs%20the%20king%20that%20he%20was%20performing%20penance%20to%20find%20a%20place%20in%20heaven.%20Rama%20punishes%20the%20Shudra%20for%20his%20transgression%20by%20cutting%20off%20his%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20writes%20that%20to%20blame%20Ram%20for%20wantonly%20killing%20Shambuk%20was%20to%20misunderstand%20the%20situation.%20As%20a%20king%2C%20Ram%20was%20bound%20to%20maintain%20the%20Chaturvarna%20(four-tier%20caste%20system%20with%20low%20caste%20Shudras%20at%20the%20bottom)%2C%20which%20was%20the%20basis%20of%20Ram%20Raj%2C%20said%20Ambedkar.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20was%20his%20duty%20to%20kill%20Shambuk%20for%20transgressing%20his%20class%20and%20wanting%20to%20be%20a%20Brahmin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDravidian%20movement%20social%20reformer%20E.%20V.%20Ramasamy%20%E2%80%9CPeriyar%E2%80%9D%20had%20also%20expressed%20outrage%20over%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20Shudras.%20In%20%3Cem%3EMany%20Ramayanas%3A%20The%20Diversity%20of%20a%20Narrative%20Tradition%20in%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20author%20Paula%20Richman%20writes%20that%20Periyar%20summarised%20the%20killing%20of%20Shambuk%20and%20extrapolated%20from%20it%20to%20present-day%20South%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERichman%20wrote%3A%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%99If%20there%20were%20kings%20like%20Rama%20now%2C%20what%20would%20be%20the%20fate%20of%20those%20people%20called%20Sudras%3F%E2%80%99%20he%20asks%2C%20implying%20that%20Sudras%20would%20never%20be%20safe%20from%20murder%20if%20such%20a%20king%20still%20ruled.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20references%20to%20Ambedkar%20and%20Periyar%E2%80%99s%20writings%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20Harijan%20defends%20the%20context%20of%20his%20controversial%20tweet.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20discuss%20all%20these%2C%20how%20will%20we%20teach%20the%20%3Cem%3EAnnihilation%20of%20Caste%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20students%3F%20How%20will%20we%20bring%20an%20end%20to%20religious%20and%20caste%20rigidities%3F%20If%20I%20am%20wrong%2C%20then%20even%20Ambedkar%2C%20Periyar%20and%20Jyotiba%20Phule%20are%20wrong.%20They%20all%20raised%20such%20questions.%20What%20I%20have%20said%20is%20nothing%20new%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Harijan%20later%20deleted%20his%20tweet%20on%20Ram%20and%20Krishna%2C%20he%20said%20he%20stands%20by%20the%20message%20he%20wanted%20to%20convey.%20His%20conviction%2C%20and%20disdain%20for%20caste%20and%20ills%20of%20the%20Hindu%20faith%2C%20are%20rooted%20in%20his%20lived%20experience%20as%20a%20Jatav%2FChamar%20(Dalit%20sub-caste)%20from%20an%20impoverished%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Not%20human%20enough%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20was%20born%20in%20a%20village%20in%20Gorakhpur%20in%20eastern%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20His%20grandmother%20used%20to%20cut%20umbilical%20cords%20of%20new-born%20babies.%20In%20return%2C%20she%20would%20have%20rotis%20thrown%20down%20at%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%E2%80%99s%20father%20worked%20as%20a%20harwah%20(full-time%20in-house%20labourer)%20who%20toiled%20both%20on%20the%20field%20as%20well%20as%20inside%20the%20house%20of%20the%20dominant%20caste%20zamindar.%20In%20return%2C%20he%20got%20food.%20But%20the%20quality%20of%20food%20was%20bad%20and%20the%20mistress%20of%20the%20house%20often%20served%20him%20left-overs.%20In%20the%20village%2C%20poor%20Dalit%20families%20like%20Harijan%E2%80%99s%20would%20often%20resort%20to%20eating%20gobrah%20roti%20to%20fill%20their%20stomach.%20These%20rotis%20were%20made%20from%20grains%20collected%20after%20washing%20cow%20dung.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnhappy%20with%20this%20setup%2C%20Harijan%E2%80%99s%20father%20left%20the%20work%20at%20the%20zamindar%E2%80%99s%20and%20migrated%20to%20West%20Bengal%2C%20where%20he%20got%20associated%20with%20the%20Naxalite%20movement.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20worker%20of%20the%20Naxalite%20movement%2C%20he%20even%20made%20bombs%20for%20a%20while%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalled%20Harijan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20father%20then%20joined%20a%20coal%20mine%20in%20Asansol%20as%20a%20worker.%20The%20family%20lived%20in%20a%20colony%20with%20other%20migrant%20workers%20from%20UP%20and%20Bihar.%20Harijan%20spent%20his%20childhood%20in%20difficult%20circumstances.%20The%20colony%20did%20not%20provide%20him%20the%20atmosphere%20to%20study.%20In%20the%20evenings%2C%20men%20would%20play%20cards%2C%20get%20drunk%20or%20often%20get%20into%20fights.%20But%20the%20support%20he%20received%20from%20his%20school%20teachers%20ensured%20he%20stayed%20motivated%20to%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Bengal%20he%20studied%20in%20a%20Hindi-medium%20government%20school%20from%20class%201%20to%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20also%20remembers%20that%20in%20Bengal%20he%20would%20often%20join%20other%20workers%20to%20steal%20coal%20from%20mines%20that%20had%20closed%20for%20business.%20He%20could%20relate%20it%20to%20his%20experience%20in%20his%20village%20in%20Gorakhpur%20where%20he%20often%20picked%20sugarcane%2C%20peas%20and%20sweet%20potato%20from%20other%E2%80%99s%20farms%20to%20beat%20hunger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Harijan%E2%80%99s%20memories%20are%20not%20restricted%20to%20poverty%20and%20financial%20constraints.%20Growing%20up%20in%20faraway%20Bengal%2C%20too%2C%20he%20faced%20casteism%20and%20saw%20the%20caste%20divisions%20within%20the%20labourers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20members%20of%20the%20Yadav%20and%20barber%20caste%20and%20even%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-pasi%5C%22%3EPasis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20are%20themselves%20Dalits%2C%20would%20pass%20casteist%20remarks%20at%20me%20about%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chamar%5C%22%3EChamar%3C%2Fa%3E%20caste.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-yadav%5C%22%3EYadav%3C%2Fa%3E%20man%20would%20often%20tease%20me%20by%20distorting%20the%20popular%20song%20%E2%80%98O%E2%80%99maria%2C%20O%E2%80%99maria%E2%80%99%20to%20%E2%80%98O%E2%80%99Chamariya%2C%20O%E2%80%99%20Chamariya%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Harijan.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20bullying%20was%20so%20normal%20that%20I%20had%20developed%20so%20much%20inferiority%20complex%20that%20I%20started%20to%20believe%20I%20was%20not%20human%20enough.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20was%20in%20class%20six%20or%20seven%20when%20while%20reading%20a%20book%20on%20Buddha%20he%20started%20to%20wonder%20about%20untouchability%20and%20caste%20discrimination%20and%20related%20it%20to%20his%20life.%20The%20turning%20point%20came%20when%20an%20upper%20caste%20tuition%20teacher%20made%20casteist%20remarks%20against%20another%20Dalit%20student%20dismissing%20reservation%20as%20a%20charity%20served%20by%20tax%20money%20of%20upper%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20was%20offended%20by%20this%20and%20stood%20up%20for%20his%20classmate.%20However%2C%20for%20speaking%20up%2C%20he%20was%20thrown%20out%20of%20the%20class.%20The%20episode%20made%20him%20furious%20and%20he%20gradually%20stopped%20worshipping%20Hindu%20deities.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20incident%20made%20me%20rebel%20against%20Hindu%20faith%20and%20caste%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131715%2FIMG-20231122-WA0140.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131715%2FIMG-20231122-WA0140.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131715%2FIMG-20231122-WA0140-300x135.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131715%2FIMG-20231122-WA0140-1024x459.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686530%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22538%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVikram%20Harijan%20with%20his%20students.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Backlash%20from%20a%20deity%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20was%20still%20young%20and%20yet%20to%20discover%20the%20writings%20of%20Ambedkar%20and%20Periyar.%20His%20initial%20influence%20came%20in%20the%20form%20of%20reformist%20ideas%20of%20Raja%20Ram%20Mohan%20Roy%2C%20who%20had%20opposed%20idol%20worship%20and%20denounced%20the%20caste%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Harijan%20started%20opposing%20idol%20worship%2C%20he%20caused%20a%20stir%20among%20his%20classmates%20by%20refusing%20to%20give%20the%20customary%20donation%20for%20Saraswati%20Puja.%20Stunned%20by%20his%20defiance%2C%20his%20fellow%20students%20dared%20him%20to%20perform%20an%20outrageous%20dare%20to%20prove%20his%20conviction.%20They%20asked%20him%20to%20urinate%20on%20the%20idol%20of%20a%20Hindu%20deity.%20He%20went%20to%20a%20nearby%20temple%20and%20performed%20the%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20from%20his%20childhood%20came%20back%20to%20haunt%20him%20in%202019%2C%20when%20he%20was%20already%20teaching%20at%20the%20Allahabad%20University.%20In%20August%20that%20year%2C%20a%20research%20scholar%2C%20also%20a%20Dalit%2C%20out%20of%20personal%20vendetta%20uploaded%20an%20old%20video%20of%20Harijan%20(recorded%20at%20a%20private%20event%20at%20a%20hostel%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20Ambedkar%20Jayanti%20on%20April%2014%2C%202017)%20in%20which%20he%20brags%20how%20as%20a%20student%20he%20had%20insulted%20a%20Hindu%20deity%20by%20urinating%20over%20it%20but%20faced%20no%20backlash%20from%20the%20deity.%20Harijan%20said%20he%20narrated%20the%20experience%20to%20the%20students%20as%20he%20wanted%20to%20bust%20their%20fears%20associated%20with%20religion%20and%20divine%20punishment%2C%20and%20not%20to%20hurt%20religious%20sentiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20university%20saw%20it%20differently%20and%20served%20him%20a%20notice%20following%20a%20complaint%20by%20a%20delegation%20of%20students%20who%20were%20offended%20by%20his%20comments.%20A%20student%20of%20the%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Vidhyarthi%20Parishad%20even%20lodged%20a%20police%20complaint%20against%20him.%20Following%20the%20uproar%20over%20his%20comments%2C%20Harijan%20feared%20he%20could%20be%20lynched%20and%20even%20requested%20authorities%20to%20grant%20him%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20completed%20his%20intermediate%20schooling%20from%20Gorakhpur%20and%20graduated%20from%20Gorakhpur%20University%2C%20before%20completing%20his%20PhD%20from%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20on%20%E2%80%98Occupational%20caste%20groups%20and%20English%20east%20India%20company%20in%20Madras%20during%2017%20and%2018%20centuries%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Allahabad%20University%2C%20he%20also%20teaches%20about%20marginalised%20communities%20in%20Indian%20history%20and%20includes%20text%20on%20caste%2C%20Ambedkar%2C%20Phule%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENotices%20and%20a%20space%20for%20discussion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202021%2C%20he%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20welcoming%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20step%20to%20remove%20caste%20names%20from%20vehicles%2C%20and%20requested%20him%20to%20issue%20guidelines%20to%20remove%20caste%20names%20prefixed%20and%20suffixed%20on%20the%20shops%20of%20public%20and%20private%20shops%20and%20industries.%20As%20examples%2C%20he%20cited%20Aggarwal%20Sweets%2C%20Jaiswal%20Cloth%20Bhandar%2C%20Pandit%20Kachuri%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202021%2C%20the%20National%20Commission%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20took%20cognisance%20of%20a%20news%20report%20in%20which%20Harijan%20had%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20caste%20discrimination%20on%20campus%20and%20that%20marks%20were%20given%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20caste.%20The%20varsity%20asked%20him%20to%20explain%20the%20basis%20of%20allegations%20along%20with%20documentary%20proof.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20varsity%20had%20also%20issued%20him%20a%20show%20cause%20notice%20after%20he%20sent%20a%20representation%20to%20the%20NCSC%20regarding%20alleged%20mental%20harassment%20and%20discrimination%20by%20AU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarijan%20feels%20there%20is%20little%20space%20to%20debate%20and%20discuss%20complex%20issues%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20rigidity%20and%20taboo%20in%20religions.%20It%E2%80%99s%20essential%20to%20question%20rigidities%20in%20all%20faiths%2C%20be%20it%20Hindu%2C%20Islam%2C%20Sikh%20or%20others%2C%20he%20argues.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20was%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20made%20for%20if%20not%20to%20provide%20space%20for%20these%20discussions%20that%20formed%20the%20basis%20for%20similar%20movements%20and%20revolutions%20in%20France%2C%20Russia%2C%20England%20and%20USA%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20offended%20by%20Harijan%E2%80%99s%20views%20often%20accuse%20him%20of%20selectively%20targeting%20Hindu%20faith.%20He%20said%20he%20talks%20more%20about%20the%20rigidities%20of%20the%20Hindu%20religion%20as%20he%20was%20born%20into%20it.%20%E2%80%9CI%20talk%20about%20the%20Hindu%20religion%20because%20Hindu%20dharm%20made%20me%20a%20Chamar.%20It%20made%20me%20eat%20gobrah%20roti%20as%20a%20child.%20My%20first%20fight%20is%20against%20the%20caste%20structure%20of%20Hinduism%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20landing%20in%20controversy%20and%20finding%20himself%20in%20the%20radar%20of%20a%20Hindu%20nationalist%20government%2C%20Harijan%20is%20defiant.%20He%20feels%20it%20is%20his%20right%20to%20educate%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20about%20systemic%20caste%20oppression%2C%20and%20infuse%20rationality%2C%20scientific%20thinking%20and%20ideas%20of%20enlightenment%20in%20his%20students.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20should%20not%20escape%20discussion%20through%20the%20hollow%20excuse%20of%20hurt%20religious%20sentiments%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Harijan%2C%20who%20has%20on%20many%20occasions%20expressed%20threat%20to%20his%20life%2C%20fears%20he%20might%20face%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20other%20rationalists%20such%20as%20Govind%20Pansare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20may%20be%20shot%20dead%20for%20my%20views.%20But%20what%20is%20the%20meaning%20of%20being%20educated%20if%20I%20cannot%20stand%20up%20for%20rationality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701071347000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27131120%2FIMG-20231122-WA0134.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fvikram-harijan-allahabad-university-hindu-deities%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Allahabad%20University%20professor%20is%20battling%20police%20cases%2C%20varsity%20raps%20on%20his%20knuckles%20and%20volleys%20of%20harassment%20over%20his%20comments%20against%20the%20caste%20structure%20of%20Hinduism.%20But%20he%20is%20unrelenting.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fvikram-harijan-allahabad-university-hindu-deities%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Record%20numbers%20sit%20for%20China%20civil%20service%20exam%2C%20hoping%20for%20job%20security%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701070773000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105529490%2Cimgsize-108918.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Frecord-numbers-sit-for-china-civil-service-exam-hoping-for-job-security%2Farticleshow%2F105528810.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105528810.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonica